{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"lun3z8bba02pxnb9w8c92zv","title":"Terminology","desc":"","updated":1647378427210,"created":1647376735186,"custom":{},"fname":"ser216.software-testing.terminology","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"d08052b53dfccd4064e4c61dfc5578ef","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"ser216.software-testing.terminology","id":"lun3z8bba02pxnb9w8c92zv","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"ser216.software-testing.terminology","alias":"failure","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":90,"offset":215},"end":{"line":10,"column":145,"offset":270},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"ser216.software-testing.terminology","anchorHeader":"Failure"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"ser216.software-testing.terminology","id":"lun3z8bba02pxnb9w8c92zv","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"ser216.software-testing.terminology","alias":"error","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":70,"offset":372},"end":{"line":17,"column":131,"offset":433},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"ser216.software-testing.terminology","anchorHeader":"Erroneous state"}},{"from":{"fname":"ser216.software-testing","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":40,"offset":40},"indent":[]},"value":"ser216.software-testing.terminology","alias":"ser216.software-testing.terminology"},{"from":{"fname":"ser216.software-testing.terminology","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":90,"offset":215},"end":{"line":10,"column":145,"offset":270},"indent":[]},"value":"ser216.software-testing.terminology","alias":"failure"},{"from":{"fname":"ser216.software-testing.terminology","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":70,"offset":372},"end":{"line":17,"column":131,"offset":433},"indent":[]},"value":"ser216.software-testing.terminology","alias":"error"}],"anchors":{"failure":{"type":"header","text":"Failure","value":"failure","line":8,"column":0,"depth":2},"erroneous-state":{"type":"header","text":"Erroneous state","value":"erroneous-state","line":12,"column":0,"depth":2},"fault":{"type":"header","text":"Fault","value":"fault","line":18,"column":0,"depth":2},"validation":{"type":"header","text":"Validation","value":"validation","line":25,"column":0,"depth":2},"examples":{"type":"header","text":"Examples","value":"examples","line":29,"column":0,"depth":2},"dealing-with-errors-failures-and-faults":{"type":"header","text":"Dealing with errors, failures, and faults","value":"dealing-with-errors-failures-and-faults","line":45,"column":0,"depth":2},"another-view-on-dealing-with-faults":{"type":"header","text":"Another view on dealing with faults","value":"another-view-on-dealing-with-faults","line":56,"column":0,"depth":3},"taxonomy-for-fault-handling":{"type":"header","text":"Taxonomy for fault handling","value":"taxonomy-for-fault-handling","line":73,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"b66meq2q93z6abjbxrkmcdo","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"terminology\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#terminology\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Terminology</h1>\n<h2 id=\"failure\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#failure\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Failure</h2>\n<p>Any deviation of the observed behavior from the specified behavior is a failure.</p>\n<h2 id=\"erroneous-state\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#erroneous-state\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Erroneous state</h2>\n<pre><code>Error\n</code></pre>\n<p>When the system is in an erroneous state, further processing by the system can lead to a <a href=\"/notes/notes/lun3z8bba02pxnb9w8c92zv#Failure\">failure</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"fault\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#fault\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Fault</h2>\n<pre><code>Bug\nDefect\n</code></pre>\n<p>A fault, bug, or defect is the mechanical or algorithmic cause of an <a href=\"/notes/notes/lun3z8bba02pxnb9w8c92zv#Erroneous state\">error</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"validation\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#validation\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Validation</h2>\n<p>Validation is the activity of checking for deviations between the observed behavior of a system and its specification.</p>\n<h2 id=\"examples\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#examples\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Examples</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Faults in the interface specification</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Mismatch between what the client needs and what the server offers</li>\n<li>Mismatch between requirements and implementation</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Algorithmic faults</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Missing initialization</li>\n<li>Incorrect branching condition</li>\n<li>Missing test for <code>null</code></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Mechanical faults</strong> (most difficult to find)\n<ul>\n<li>Operating temperature outside of equipment's specifications</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Errors</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><code>null</code> reference errors</li>\n<li>Concurrency errors</li>\n<li>Exceptions</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"dealing-with-errors-failures-and-faults\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#dealing-with-errors-failures-and-faults\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Dealing with errors, failures, and faults</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Modular redundancy</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Adding additional components to a system to mitigate the failure of a component by reproducing the behavior of the component in a different environment\n<ul>\n<li>Example: Adding a backup battery to a laptop</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Declaring the bug as a feature</strong> (doing nothing)</li>\n<li><strong>Patching</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Addressing the error by modifying the code</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Testing</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Adding additional tests to the system to ensure that the error is not reintroduced</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"another-view-on-dealing-with-faults\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#another-view-on-dealing-with-faults\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Another view on dealing with faults</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fault avoidance</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Done before system is released</li>\n<li>Use methodology to reduce complexity</li>\n<li>Use configuration management to prevent inconsistency</li>\n<li>Apply verification to prevent algorithmic faults</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Fault detection</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Done while system is running</li>\n<li>Testing to detect faults</li>\n<li>Debugging to find and resolve faults</li>\n<li>Monitoring to deliver information about state of system</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Fault tolerance</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Done after system failure</li>\n<li>Exception handling</li>\n<li>Modular redundancy</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"taxonomy-for-fault-handling\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#taxonomy-for-fault-handling\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Taxonomy for fault handling</h2>\n<div class=\"mermaid\">\n  flowchart BT\n    UT[Unit Testing] --> Testing\n    IT[Integration Testing] --> Testing\n    ST[System Testing] --> Testing\n\n    Testing --> FD[Fault Detection]\n    Debugging --> FD[Fault Detection]\n    Testing &#x3C;--> Debugging\n\n    Methodology --> FA[Fault Avoidance]\n    Verification --> FA\n    CM[Configuration Management] --> FA\n\n    AT[Atomic Transactions] --> FT[Fault Tolerance]\n    MR[Modular Redundancy] --> FT\n    \n    FA --> FH[Fault Handling]\n    FD --> FH\n    FT --> FH\n</div>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/notes/b66meq2q93z6abjbxrkmcdo\">Software Testing</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/notes/lun3z8bba02pxnb9w8c92zv\">Terminology</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"6YxiIDvTOeKoHyAaqqzY9","title":"Notes","desc":"","updated":1655764869385,"created":1641245237998,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"fc07e211d902512814feeef3187746c9","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"6YxiIDvTOeKoHyAaqqzY9","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"typescript","alias":"typescript","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":3,"offset":22},"end":{"line":4,"column":17,"offset":36},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"typescript"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"6YxiIDvTOeKoHyAaqqzY9","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"luau","alias":"luau","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":3,"offset":39},"end":{"line":5,"column":11,"offset":47},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"luau"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"6YxiIDvTOeKoHyAaqqzY9","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"ser222","alias":"SER 222 - Data Structures & Algorithms","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":3,"offset":67},"end":{"line":9,"column":52,"offset":116},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"ser222"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"6YxiIDvTOeKoHyAaqqzY9","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"ser216","alias":"SER 216 - \"Software Enterprise\" aka Intro to Software Design","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":3,"offset":119},"end":{"line":10,"column":74,"offset":190},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"ser216"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"6Yx